- - - ( Reusable Blade ) - - -

** ( Template Inheritance ):  

- allows templates to become dynamic or be changed,
  by the template that is inheriting it 

  this can be done w/code: {@extends('template_name');}




** ( "@yield('...')" & "section('...') @endsection" ):

- "@yield('...')", a directive used to make a section dynamic

- "section('...') @endsection", a directive used to add / change 
  the values under the "@yield('...')"


  ( Example Code ):

   {home.blade.php}:   

   @extends("this_layout")
   
   @section("title") Home @endsection  or  @section( "title" , "Home" ) //for small one liners
   @section("content") Contents of Home @endsection 



   {this_layout.blade.php}:  

   <main> 
    <h1> @yield("title"); </h1> //replaced by "Home" 
    <p> @yield("content"); </p> //replaced by "Contents of Home" 
   </main>
   //Values are replaced by the home.blade.php




** ( "@section('...') - @show" ):

- this directive allows an entire section of 
  a template, to become a "yield"


 ( Example Code ):

  {home.blade.php}:   

  @extends("this_layout")
  
  @section("main")
   <div> 
    <h3> Default Title </h3> 
    <b> Default Paragraph </b> 
   </div>
  @endsection



  {this_layout.blade.php}:  

  @section("main")
   <main> 
    <h1> Default Title </h1> 
    <p> Default Paragraph </p> 
   </main>
  @show 
  //Everything in this @section('main') - @show 
  //will be replcaed by the one in the home.blade.php




** ( "@parent" ):   

- this directive, is used inside a "@section(...) - @endsection", to
  add the content from a "parent layout's section", before applying 
  the change


  ( Example Code ):  

  {home.blade.php}:   

   @extends("this_layout")
    
    @section("main")
     @parent //( Main Icon(s) 1 - 3, is added here )
     Additional Icon (1)
     Additional Icon (2)
     Additional Icon (3) 
    @endsection



  {this_layout.blade.php}:  

   @section("main")
    Main Icon (1)
    Main Icon (2)
    Main Icon (3)
   @show 
   //Everything in this @section('main') - @show 
   //will be replcaed by the one in the home.blade.php



  


